THE
SECRET
OF
MARS.

Some
people
say
that
the
planet
Mars
is
uninhabited.
But
this
is
not
true,

for
I
have
been
there
and
seen
it.

Many
centuries
ago,
the
Martians
fought
their
last
great
war
;

cen

turies

they

life
scientifically
perfect.

But
for
all
that,
they
were
not
content;
and
their
planet,
like
their
hearts,

began
growing
colder
every
year.

Then
one
day
they
suddenly
decided
to
build
a
great
tower
to
a
forgotten

God
;

of

decided

no

of

and

hands.

Centuries
they
must
have
laboured,
for
the
building
as

is
immense

in
desolation.
It
is
surrounded
with
a
forest
of
columns
for
ten
miles;
at
the

intersection
of
enormous
aisles,
poised
above
the
glory
of
huge
leaping
arches,

stands
the
lantern-tower
unfinished,
ten
thousand
feet
high.

Upon
the
pavement
below

is

is

in
death.
